Program: Last Word
Title: 08/10/2010
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00v1rm4
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 10 Oct 2010
On Last Word this week: Metropolitan Police Commissioner Sir Robert Mark who cleaned up widespread corruption among the forces detectives Sir Norman Wisdom - whose performances as a lovable underdog stemmed from rejection and poverty in his childhood The influential moral philosopher Philippa Foot who put her principles into action by working for Oxfam Mahinder Singh Pujji - who was thought to be the last remaining Sikh and Indian fighter pilot from the second world war And Gloria Stuart, the Hollywood actress who was nominated for an Oscar for playing a one hundred year old survivor in "Titanic". Show less